(iii) Supports coordination and implementation of programmes to improve Iraq’s capacity to provide essential services and donor coordination through the International Reconstruction Fund Facility for Iraq (IRFFI);

(iv) Encourages economic reform, capacity-building and sustainable development conditions, including through coordination with national and regional organizations, civil society, donors, and international financial institutions;

(v) Promotes development of effective civil, social and essential services, including through training and conferences in Iraq;

(vi) Notes the contributions of UN agencies, funds and programmes under unified leadership of the Secretary-General’s Special Representative for Iraq;

(c) Also promotes protection of human rights and judicial and legal reform to strengthen the rule of law;

2. … 

3. Recognizes the important role of the Multi-National Force Iraq (MNF-I) in supporting UNAMI, including security and logistical support, and that security is essential for UNAMI;

4. Calls on Member States to provide UNAMI with necessary financial, logistical and security resources;

5. Intends to review UNAMI’s mandate in twelve months or sooner, if requested by the Government of Iraq;

6. Requests the Secretary-General to report to the Council within three months and on a quarterly basis thereafter on UNAMI operations;

7. Decides to remain seized of the matter.
